<column pad-="2 1" gap-="1">
    <column gap-="1">
        <p
            >Salvadoran Reclamation is a top-down shooter I made for JS13K 2024
            where you play as a soldier from the Salvadoran Army against gang
            members across the country</p
        >
        <ul>
            <li>
                <strong>URL</strong>: <a
                    href="https://ironcladdev.github.io/salvadoran-reclamation/"
                    target="_blank"
                    >https://ironcladdev.github.io/salvadoran-reclamation/</a
                >
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>GitHub</strong>: <a
                    href="https://github.com/IroncladDev/salvadoran-reclamation"
                    target="_blank"
                    >https://github.com/IroncladDev/salvadoran-reclamation</a
                >
            </li>
        </ul>
    </column>

    <strong><mark fg-="green-fg-dim">Current Status</mark></strong>

    <column pad-="2 0" gap-="1">
        <p
            >I stopped maintaining the project after JS13K 2024 ended. I
            published the game to github pages and archived the project on <mark
                fg-="purple-fg">Jun 23, 2026</mark
            ></p
        >
    </column>

    <strong><mark fg-="green-fg-dim">History</mark></strong>

    <column pad-="2 0" gap-="1">
        <p
            ><mark fg-="purple-fg">Aug 13, 2024</mark> - The JS13K competition starts
            mid-August and lasts until mid-September. The theme is "Triskidephobia"
            (fear of the number 13). The only thing that comes to my mind is the
            <strong>MS-13</strong> gang in El Salvador.</p
        >
        <p
            >I have a lot of fun building, tweaking, designing, and debugging my
            game. The 13-kilobyte limit seems generous at first but then slowly
            starts to become a problem later. I end up removing some features.</p
        >
        <p
            ><mark fg-="purple-fg">September 12, 2024</mark> - I release the finalized
            project after burning myself out by being on the computer for 16 hours
            a day and decide to never do JS13K while simultaneously working a full-time
            job ever again.</p
        >
    </column>

    <strong><mark fg-="green-fg-dim">Technologies Used</mark></strong>

    <column pad-="2 0" gap-="1">
        <p><mark fg-="blue-fg" bg-="blue-bg">&#xe8ca; TypeScript</mark></p>
    </column>
</column>
